ohai .vim

1_ install macvim if you're on, um, a mac (needed to get vim with +ruby)
$ brew install macvim --override-system-vim

2_ clone this bad boy into ~/.vim
$ git clone git@github.com:bergren2/dotvim.git ~/.vim

3_ update those submodules
$ git submodule update --init

4_ install stuff -- .vimrc, .gvimrc, .ackrc, and command-t (make sure to use system ruby!)
$ ruby ~/.vim/install.rb

thank yous go to zach belzer, since i basically stole this from him when he wasn't looking. (:
https://github.com/zbelzer/dotvim

one day i'll vim stuff on linux and i'll update this then

ec_ (extra credit!!!) (ﾉ◕ヮ◕)ﾉ*:･ﾟ✧*:･ﾟ✧
since these bundles get out of date, run the following from .vim/ to use the latest packages

$ git submodule foreach git pull origin master
$ git add bundle/
$ git ci -m 'woohoo can haz updated bundles!'

and remember... stay out of trouble! (╯°□°)╯︵ɯıʌ
